dc_title_s: Healthcare Emergency Readiness Coalition Regions, Wisconsin 2020
dc_description_s: This data represents healthcare emergency readiness coalition region boundaries for Wisconsin in 2020. [This dataset contains the boundaries for the Wisconsin Healthcare Emergency Readiness Coalition regions. In 2014, Wisconsin established seven healthcare coalition regions to coordinate how public health, healthcare institutions, and first responder agencies, such as police, fire and emergency medical services (EMS), will manage their efforts to enact a uniform and unified response to an emergency, including a mass casualty or other catastrophic event. For more information please visit the Wisconsin Department of Health Services website: https://www.dhs.wisconsin.gov/preparedness/healthcare/index.htm]
